The module is a fork of the original huawegeneric-ril
which can be found at https://github.com/DerArtem/huaweigeneric-ril
It has been tweaked to work with the Archos G9 Series of Android Tablets

Successful Testing has been carried out using Huawei E1752Cu E173s-1 and an E1750
The Function correctly

* it required /etc/ppp/init_pppd_gprs for pppd.
	
	PPPD_TTY=$(/system/bin/getprop ril.pppd_tty)
	if test -z "$PPPD_TTY" ; then
     		/system/bin/setprop ril.pppd_tty /dev/ttyUSB0 
	fi
	PPPD_PID=
	/system/bin/setprop "net.gprs.ppp-exit" ""

	/system/bin/log -t pppd "Starting pppd"

	/system/bin/pppd $PPPD_TTY 460800 $* debug kdebug 8 dump linkname gprs unit 1 crtscts usepeerdns noauth \
	defaultroute noipdefault ipcp-accept-local ipcp-accept-remote ipcp-max-failure 30 lcp-echo-interval 5 lcp-echo-failure 30 \
	modem dump connect "/system/xbin/chat -v -t 500 -f /system/etc/chatscripts/gprs_start"


	PPPD_EXIT=$?
	PPPD_PID=$!

	/system/bin/log -t pppd "pppd exited with $PPPD_EXIT"

	/system/bin/setprop "net.gprs.ppp-exit" "$PPPD_EXIT"
	
	service usb_modeswitch /system/bin/usbs
	user root
	disabled
	oneshot